The AI writing exercise layout did not fit smaller screens well: the prompt and response panes remained too wide, and the feedback cards stayed in a two-column layout. This change makes the writing UI collapse cleanly on mobile so each major panel fits the viewport.

- **Writing exercise mobile layout**
  - Stack the prompt pane and response pane vertically on screens up to 768px.
  - Remove desktop width constraints so both panes use full mobile width.
  - Relax overflow behavior in the prompt panel to avoid clipped content.
  - Allow the writing area header to wrap instead of forcing horizontal squeeze.

- **Feedback/results mobile layout**
  - Change the writing results grid from two columns to a single column on mobile.
  - Stack Task 1 / Task 2 feedback cards one per row.
  - Convert the combined score header and per-card result headers to vertical layouts where needed to prevent overflow.

- **Versioning**
  - Bump the plugin version to `19.6`.

```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  #ielts-writing-container,
  .ielts-writing-results-grid {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  #ielts-writing-left-col,
  #ielts-writing-right-col {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 100%;
  }
}
```
